@Node "Archive@Project@SavePreferences"

The "Save preferences" Item

This item saves the preferences of Archive.

Note:
Title catalogs will automatically be saved when changed. So using
"Save preferences" is not necessary.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@LoadPreferences"

The "Load preferences" Item

This item loads previously saved preferences of Archive.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@SetupPrinter"

The "Setup printer" Item

This item starts SYS:Prefs/Printer to modify the printer preferences.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@Print"

The "Printer" Item

This item prints the catalog of the current CD.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@About"

The "About MusicBox" Item

This item shows information about Archive and your hardware.
@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@Iconify"

The "Iconify" Item

This item iconifies Archive.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@Help"

The "Help" Item

This item shows this AmigaGuide file.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Project@Quit"

The "Quit Archive" Item

This item quits Archive.

@EndNode


@Node "Archive@Preferences@AutoSave"

The "Auto-save catalog" Item

If activated, Archive automatically saves an edited CD-ROM catalog
without confirmation. Otherwise, Archive asks you if you want
to save it.
@EndNode

@Node "Archive@Search"

The "Search title" Item

Here you can let Archive search a title. Of course you may use
standard AmigaDOS patterns: ? for one char and #? for several chars.
The search is case insensitive (a = A).

Example:
A#? finds all titles beginning with A or a.
xx?yy finds e.g. xxayy xxTyy but not xxTTyy.
@EndNode

@Node "Archive@Startup"

ToolTypes and Arguments of Archive


Starting Archive:

Archive can be started from Workbench or CLI/Shell.

Arguments for CLI/Shell call:

-q oder QUIET:
  Archive starts iconified; useful for Start in S:User-Startup etc.

-u oder US:
  MusicBox ignores locale settings and starts with English user interface.

-l oder LOWRES:
  This option forces Archive to use a resolution of 640x256, although
  a higher resolution can be used.

-i oder IGNORETOOLTYPES:
  All ToolTypes entries will be ignored.


ToolTypes entries

QUIET=ON|OFF
  Archive starts iconified (ON) or not iconified (OFF)

FASTEXIT=ON|OFF
  Archive will quit, when clicked on the close button (ON) or
  be iconified (OFF)

US=ON|OFF
  ON:  Locale will be ignored
  OFF: Archive uses locale

LOWRES=ON|OFF
  see -l/LOWRES
@EndNode


